            <p>This article profiles 19 essential operational tools used in daily contact center workflows. Each tool is defined by its function in digital contact environments. Evaluation criteria include routing intelligence, agent assist features, analytics integration, and audit support. Practical use cases demonstrate improvements in resolution time, agent productivity, and compliance rates. The covered tools include Automatic Call Distributors (ACD), Interactive Voice Response (IVR), and Computer Telephony Integration (CTI). Additional tools include Workforce Management (WFM), Speech Analytics, Real-Time Dashboards, and Role-Based Access Controls.
